00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:11,163
He has memories with him
in all sorts of places.

230
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:15,434
It really shows that everyone uses these
two months differently, in their own way.

231
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:18,037
He doesn't like yogurt,
but his partner does.

232
00:12:18,104 --> 00:12:19,705
So he buys it when it's on sale.

233
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:24,510
It's like something straight out of one
of those Yuji Sakamoto movies, isn't it?

234
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:26,278
That's true.

235
00:12:26,345 --> 00:12:29,115
B.T.C.
US, JOURNEY, AND COFFEE

236
00:12:29,181 --> 00:12:32,952
We've never really had a one-on-one
conversation together,

237
00:12:33,018 --> 00:12:35,154
and I've been wanting to talk to you.

238
00:12:35,221 --> 00:12:36,655
So, that's why I chose you.

239
00:12:36,722 --> 00:12:40,092
Well, okay. Didn't you mention
something about coming out?

240
00:12:40,159 --> 00:12:41,393
Yeah, I did.

241
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:43,462
- Do you think you will?
- I don't know.

242
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:48,234
