243
00:12:48,734 --> 00:12:50,870
But why do you want to come out?

244
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:54,340
I want to be accepted.

245
00:12:54,406 --> 00:12:56,609
Hmm, okay.

246
00:12:58,144 --> 00:13:01,113
My mother passed away
when I was in kindergarten.

247
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,515
Oh, really?

248
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:06,886
So my father's been raising me
all by himself until now.

249
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:07,820
Okay.

250
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:13,192
At first,
he probably couldn't do any housework,

251
00:13:13,259 --> 00:13:15,394
but he worked hard for me.

252
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:18,030
It's hard to…

253
00:13:23,702 --> 00:13:24,770
Hmm.

254
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:29,375
I mean… I'm about to cry.

255
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,279
Mmm.

256
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:35,614
Like, if I had had both parents,

257
00:13:36,348 --> 00:13:39,151
even if my father didn't accept me…

258
00:13:39,218 --> 00:13:41,620
- Maybe so.
- Maybe my mother would have.

259
00:13:41,687 --> 00:13:44,690
So, I'd still have a family.

260
00:13:45,191 --> 00:13:46,725
But I only have one parent.

261
00:13:47,793 --> 00:13:51,163
If he rejects me,
I won't have any family left at all.

262
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,898
I see.

263
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,401
It's difficult.

264
00:13:56,368 --> 00:13:59,772
So I don't want to think about it,
to be honest.

265
00:14:00,272 --> 00:14:02,141
A parent isn't a friend.

266
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:04,043
Mmm.

267
00:14:04,109 --> 00:14:07,513
I can't ignore the risk of not being

268
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:12,384
accepted by my father
if I were to tell him.

269
00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:16,622
The thought of that
really makes me want to forget about it.

270
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:25,231
But ever since I realized
I was bound to run into this issue,

271
00:14:25,297 --> 00:14:28,267
I haven't been able to stop
thinking about what to do.

272
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:29,268
Mmm.

273
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:33,372
You haven't been talking about it
that much, right? Like, with everyone.

274
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:36,208
- I started to think it was pointless.
- Oh, yeah?

275
00:14:36,275 --> 00:14:38,944
Well, in the end,
it's up to you to decide.

276
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:43,682
If you hear other people's perspectives,
it might change the way you think.

277
00:14:43,749 --> 00:14:45,451
It might help you make up your mind.

278
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:50,356
There are a lot of people in this house
who are in similar situations.

279
00:14:50,923 --> 00:14:53,092
That's true. I could ask them.

280
00:14:53,158 --> 00:14:55,494
I was struggling with it personally,

281
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:59,164
but I hadn't really tried
asking people for advice.

282
00:15:03,302 --> 00:15:04,770
Mmm.

283
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:06,639
I think it's a really big hurdle

284
00:15:06,705 --> 00:15:09,008
for anyone who has
this kind of decision to make.

285
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:12,511
Coming out as gay to a father
is a much bigger hurdle

286
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:15,748
than coming out as gay to a mother,
for obvious reasons.

287
00:15:15,814 --> 00:15:17,016
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

288
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:20,352
*it's a really difficult conversation
to have with a parent.

289
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:24,857
But despite his circumstances,
Ryuki still wants to tell his father.

290
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:28,594
So, he should get advice from others
and listen to their experiences.

291
00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:31,063
- Mmm.
- It won't be a waste of time.

292
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:33,098
When Jobu asked him,
"Why do you wanna come out?"

293
00:15:33,165 --> 00:15:34,066
I think he realized,

294
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:37,269
"Oh, maybe I don't have to
officially come out in the first place."

295
00:15:37,336 --> 00:15:41,440
I've always wanted to say
that coming out isn't always needed,

296
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:43,542
because it isn't always
a good thing to do.

297
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:47,613
For people who don't want to come out but
who feel like they have to do it anyway,

298
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,281
they might feel relieved to know.

299
00:15:49,348 --> 00:15:52,718
- It's totally okay. Yeah.
- Not coming out is completely acceptable.

300
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:53,619
I agree.

301
00:15:53,686 --> 00:15:55,955
- So now…
- Hiroya finally came back.

302
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:58,691
That's right.
He was supposed to be gone for two weeks.

303
00:15:58,757 --> 00:16:00,893
He said it might take longer
depending on the situation.

304
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,362
- I didn't know that.
- But he came back in ten days.

305
00:16:03,429 --> 00:16:06,999
- He came back earlier.
- He just said he'd be gone for a while.

306
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:08,133
- Right.
- Exactly.

307
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,469
But they also have
a limited time in there.

308
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:15,107
A week may seem brief to us, but for them,
this takes away from their time together.

309
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:17,676
- Time they won't be able to make up.
- You're right.

310
00:16:17,743 --> 00:16:20,546
- But Hiroya must be feeling nervous, too.
- Yeah.

311
00:16:20,612 --> 00:16:22,948
He must be wondering
what happened while he was away.

312
00:16:23,015 --> 00:16:25,317
Yeah, he has no idea that Huwei and Bomi

313
00:16:25,384 --> 00:16:29,355
have been slowly but surely getting closer
to one another over these last few days.

314
00:16:29,421 --> 00:16:30,756
- Exactly.
- He has no idea.

315
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,191
He said he could ask Bomi,

316
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:35,094
but I think he might end up
getting his feelings hurt.

317
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,796
Izaya said that William
couldn't sleep last time,

318
00:16:37,863 --> 00:16:39,765
but this time,
they could both sleep soundly.

319
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:41,967
- That I can believe.
- Has that happened to you?

320
00:16:42,034 --> 00:16:45,504
Have you ever had one of those mornings
when, after some time apart,

321
00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:48,474
you and someone from your past
end up together again?

322
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:50,576
Mister, you must've had a bunch of those.

323
00:16:50,642 --> 00:16:51,877
Well…

324
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:54,480
Now that I think about it,
I actually haven't experienced that.

325
00:16:54,546 --> 00:16:56,915
- Really? You haven't? You never reconnect?
- I mean…

326
00:16:56,982 --> 00:17:01,020
I may have experienced
the same kind of next day morning

327
00:17:01,086 --> 00:17:02,654
three years after it happened.

328
00:17:02,721 --> 00:17:04,823
- Oh, wow…
- Thank you, Mister.

329
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:07,092
- Now we know!
- Thank you for telling the truth.

330
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:10,029
- Yeah, now you know the truth about me.
- Okay, good to know!

331
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,100
The coffee truck team is working.

332
00:17:15,167 --> 00:17:17,436
- And Kazuyuki left on his own?
- He needed space.

333
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:19,304
Why can't he sleep in the Green Room?

334
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:22,441
- He just wanted some time alone.
- Mmm.

335
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:25,944
And it's not really in his nature
to stay in his room by himself

336
00:17:26,612 --> 00:17:28,113
when everyone is here.

337
00:17:28,180 --> 00:17:31,316
It's difficult for him,
so he has to force himself to be alone,

338
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,318
- Mmm.
- Or else he can't be.

339
00:17:33,986 --> 00:17:35,888
15 years, huh?

340
00:17:35,954 --> 00:17:37,823
That's something I'm not familiar with.

341
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,325
It's almost as long
as Ryuki's has been alive.

342
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:43,562
That's right.
They started dating when he was five.

343
00:17:43,629 --> 00:17:45,798
That's nuts,
