344
00:17:46,298 --> 00:17:47,766
It's hard to last that long.

345
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:50,269
I'd like to talk with him about this,
just the two of us,

346
00:17:50,335 --> 00:17:51,837
but talking with him is…

347
00:17:52,337 --> 00:17:54,573
- Yeah. I get it.
- You know? You get it, right?

348
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,475
- To go out of your way…
- I thought about asking.

349
00:17:56,542 --> 00:17:58,010
But to be honest,

350
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:01,647
I felt like I wouldn't have been able
to really relate to his story.

351
00:18:01,713 --> 00:18:03,949
I have little experience with love,

352
00:18:04,016 --> 00:18:06,685
and I've never dated
the same person for 15 years.

353
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:09,021
Well, I did ask him and he said,

354
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:13,058
"Talking with everyone has showed me
that there are many perspectives."

355
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,027
<i>"It's not about how long</i>
<i>you're with someone."</i>

356
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,595
<i>"It can be two, three or 15 years."</i>

357
00:18:16,662 --> 00:18:17,696
<i>He's right.</i>

358
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,798
<i>He said, "I'm feeling a lot of things."</i>

359
00:18:19,865 --> 00:18:21,600
- "And it's really helping me."
- Oh.

360
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,035
He said he wanted to talk more.

361
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:26,805
It must be difficult to talk about that
kind of thing with everyone, right?

362
00:18:26,872 --> 00:18:28,674
- It must be emotional.
- Yeah.

363
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:31,176
- The group shouldn't be bigger than three.
- You're right.

364
00:18:31,243 --> 00:18:33,812
When we all talk together,
there's one conversation over here,

365
00:18:33,879 --> 00:18:35,180
another over there…

366
00:18:35,247 --> 00:18:37,950
You get upset and say,
"Hey, share that with everyone."

367
00:18:39,251 --> 00:18:41,487
- Tomoaki is starting to fit in.
- He's speaking up.

368
00:18:41,553 --> 00:18:43,088
- Starting to fit in.
