what are you supposed to do after that?

422
00:20:48,981 --> 00:20:50,015
What are the rules?

423
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:53,685
Once I like someone,
I would get together with them already.

424
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:56,054
- Okay.
- Your only option is that. Yeah.

425
00:20:56,121 --> 00:20:58,857
- The only one? That's surprising.
- What? Isn't that the case?

426
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:02,694
It's simple. Are you having
second thoughts about getting together?

427
00:21:03,829 --> 00:21:09,101
I mean, I think it's a big commitment
for both of us to take, you know?

428
00:21:09,868 --> 00:21:13,805
So I can't help but think
about how much we can

429
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,375
really focus on each other.

430
00:21:16,441 --> 00:21:20,145
Yeah, but you can't know
how much you can focus on each other

431
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:21,647
unless you get together, right?

432
00:21:21,713 --> 00:21:23,348
- Absolutely,
- I guess you're right.

433
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:27,519
So, you should get together
as a means to see

434
00:21:27,586 --> 00:21:30,355
if you two can really talk
things through together.

435
00:21:30,422 --> 00:21:32,557
- Right?
- Oh, okay, I get it.

436
00:21:34,092 --> 00:21:37,796
Being apart made me think about him more.

437
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:41,867
And because I can't see him,
I was reminded of my feelings.

438
00:21:41,933 --> 00:21:43,935
"I really do like this person."

439
00:21:44,569 --> 00:21:45,737
Yeah, but…

440
00:21:46,238 --> 00:21:48,240
But it's just like you said.

441
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,976
It might also be an option to go back

442
00:21:51,043 --> 00:21:53,412
and just get together for now.

443
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:56,415
I get that, but I also wanted to see

444
00:21:57,249 --> 00:21:59,718
how much we can talk about things.

445
00:21:59,785 --> 00:22:04,489
So, what are his… Bomi's views,
on relationships? What are his…

446
00:22:04,556 --> 00:22:08,360
So, apparently,
he's never dated a guy before.

447
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:09,795
- What? Are you sure?
- Yeah.

448
00:22:09,861 --> 00:22:12,998
So I can understand that we might
clash when certain things happen,

449
00:22:13,065 --> 00:22:16,735
but since he lacks that experience,
it's like building from scratch.

450
00:22:16,802 --> 00:22:18,170
- That's good.
- But that's fine too.

451
00:22:18,236 --> 00:22:20,906
- Sounds fun.
- You can show him all sorts of fun things.

452
00:22:20,972 --> 00:22:22,507
Setting the standard yourself…

453
00:22:22,574 --> 00:22:26,011
