00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:51,103
Whoo!

462
00:22:51,169 --> 00:22:53,772
- "Will be yours!" Big responsibility.
- Thank you very much, ladies!

463
00:22:53,839 --> 00:22:56,742
- Just go for it, like an <i>o soto gari.</i>
- You want me to flip him over?

464
00:22:56,808 --> 00:23:00,746
- If you hesitate, you always get thrown.
- That's true and you know it!

465
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:04,883
Going for it without hesitation always
leads to the best outcome, right?

466
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:06,151
Anchor yourself.

467
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:08,553
- Go for it.
- Anchor yourself.

468
00:23:09,187 --> 00:23:12,057
- I'll go for it.
- You'll be a winner for sure.

469
00:23:12,557 --> 00:23:14,559
I love how they talk in judo terms.

470
00:23:14,626 --> 00:23:16,828
- Wow. An <i>o soto gari </i>of romance!
- Yeah.

471
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:26,705
- Oh, that's…
- Oh, stop.

472
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:28,774
- It's even lit up.
- Yeah, it's lit up.

473
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,808
Who did this?

474
00:23:29,875 --> 00:23:34,346
- I thought it'd be lonely without him.
- It can stay until he comes back.

475
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:38,617
- Where is Ryuki?
- Taking a day off because he has school.

476
00:23:38,683 --> 00:23:39,851
- I get it.
- I see.

477
00:23:41,052 --> 00:23:43,155
Oh! I guess I'll read it.

478
00:23:45,023 --> 00:23:45,891
Oh!

479
00:23:47,159 --> 00:23:48,693
"For today's work shift…

480
00:23:50,228 --> 00:23:51,830
Izaya will be on duty."

481
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:54,566
Okay.

482
00:23:57,402 --> 00:23:59,204
- Who will he choose?
- I wonder.

483
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:10,782
Let's work together.

484
00:24:11,516 --> 00:24:14,519
It's William? Hurry up and go. Go, go.

485
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:15,921
Have a good time.

486
00:24:27,532 --> 00:24:29,701
- There are pictures I want to take.
- What kind?

487
00:24:29,768 --> 00:24:34,239
I want this half and this half,
so when you put them together…

488
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:36,441
It'll be one picture. Sounds good.

489
00:24:38,109 --> 00:24:39,911
Say cheese.

490
00:24:44,082 --> 00:24:45,183
It's tight.

491
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:47,486
Three, two,

492
00:24:48,186 --> 00:24:49,187
one.

493
00:24:52,023 --> 00:24:53,024
Hello.

494
00:24:54,059 --> 00:24:56,294
- One small café latte…
- A café latte.

495
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:57,729
One small, okay.

496
00:24:57,796 --> 00:25:00,031
- Two small hot chocolate milks.
- Two.

497
00:25:00,098 --> 00:25:02,167
- Wanna go together?
- Mmm.

498
00:25:02,234 --> 00:25:03,168
Mmm.

499
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:06,505
- Sorry.
- Oh, no problem. Thank you.

500
00:25:06,571 --> 00:25:09,474
- Take care. Thank you.
- Okay, thank you. Thanks.

501
00:25:11,042 --> 00:25:13,111
- It's cold.
- Yeah.

502
00:25:17,983 --> 00:25:19,951
- No one around.
- Look.

503
00:25:22,153 --> 00:25:24,356
That's cute. I'll take a picture.

504
00:25:25,156 --> 00:25:27,592
- That looks great. Look.
- It looks great.

505
00:25:28,159 --> 00:25:29,394
TODAY'S SALES
4,000 YEN

506
00:25:29,461 --> 00:25:32,597
- <i>Oh, they drew a heart.</i>
- <i>They're in a great mood.</i>

507
00:25:33,598 --> 00:25:35,267
I'm glad it's the original members.

508
00:25:35,333 --> 00:25:37,168
I know, right? It's been a while.

509
00:25:37,235 --> 00:25:38,970
- Memories!
- The good ol' days!

510
00:25:39,037 --> 00:25:40,939
- So, how have you been?
- I've been good.

511
00:25:41,006 --> 00:25:43,975
- It really has been a while.
- We have a lot to talk about.

512
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:45,777
- Yeah. We do.
- Let's talk.

513
00:25:45,844 --> 00:25:48,179
- Let's all talk openly.
- Okay, let's talk.

514
00:25:48,246 --> 00:25:50,115
What should we talk about first?

515
00:25:50,181 --> 00:25:52,017
- How about Taeheon?
- Sure.

516
00:25:52,517 --> 00:25:55,487
- He's originally our favorite, right?
- Yeah, yeah, he is.

517
00:25:55,554 --> 00:25:58,723
The question is, can your favorite idol
become an actual love interest?

518
00:25:58,790 --> 00:26:00,792
- We're starting there.
- First, yeah.

519
00:26:00,859 --> 00:26:02,127
- Why not?
- Let's.

520
00:26:02,193 --> 00:26:03,795
But before we get into that specifically,

521
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:06,898
I had my own rollercoaster
romance to deal with.

522
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:09,801
I was pursuing romance
in the first half of this experience,

523
00:26:09,868 --> 00:26:12,904
but now, in the second half,
I was supporting everyone here.

524
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:15,807
But just as I was deciding to do that,

525
00:26:17,208 --> 00:26:18,276
two guys showed up.

526
00:26:18,343 --> 00:26:20,679
- Interesting.
- I mentioned this on day one.

527
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:21,980
- Right.
- You did.

528
00:26:22,047 --> 00:26:23,281
- That he's my type.
- True.

529
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:26,217
- And he shows up.
- I was overwhelmed with happiness.

530
00:26:26,284 --> 00:26:28,720
- I bet you were.
- He really was. He was nervous.

531
00:26:28,787 --> 00:26:31,089
- Super nervous, like, "What should I do?"
- Jobu was nervous.

532
00:26:31,156 --> 00:26:33,224
- I wish I could have seen that.
- Yeah.

533
00:26:33,291 --> 00:26:35,427
We ran the coffee truck,
and it was gloomy.

534
00:26:35,493 --> 00:26:38,663
- It made me feel down. It wasn't exciting.
- Things don't always work out.

535
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:42,667
I was like, "What do I do?"
Just earlier I was sitting there, right?

536
00:26:42,734 --> 00:26:45,971
- You were.
- Then he came and sat behind me.

537
00:26:46,571 --> 00:26:49,574
- My guess is he's on a plane.
- Around noon?

538
00:26:49,641 --> 00:26:51,643
I thought Kazu would be back around noon.

539
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:52,877
- He's not back.
- <i>What?</i>

540
00:26:52,944 --> 00:26:55,080
- <i>What is going on?</i>
- Get in touch?

541
00:26:55,146 --> 00:26:56,948
I don't know. I'll try texting him.

542
00:26:57,515 --> 00:26:59,884
- After he did that…
- He's so sly.

543
00:26:59,951 --> 00:27:01,586
Naturally, I was like, "Huh?"

544
00:27:01,653 --> 00:27:04,723
- It would make anyone go, "Huh?"
- It sure would make me go, "Huh?"

545
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:05,857
I'm overwhelmed.

546
00:27:05,924 --> 00:27:08,426
So stop it! Stop it!

547
00:27:10,996 --> 00:27:13,832
Yeah… I want to run the truck
with him one more time.

548
00:27:13,898 --> 00:27:16,768
I think you should. I think you should
show him more of yourself.

549
00:27:16,835 --> 00:27:19,738
- Really? True.
- You should be the one to choose Taeheon.

550
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:23,608
- Choose him and tell him, "I see you."
- I'll tell him, "I'm focused on you now."

551
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:25,143
- Tell him, "I see you."
- True.

552
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:27,646
I don't think that part has
gotten across yet, but…

553
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:29,714
Yeah, but there's one thing
you're not considering.

554
00:27:29,781 --> 00:27:31,650
Taeheon chose Huwei
when it was his turn, right?

555
00:27:31,716 --> 00:27:35,286
Mm-hm. I thought maybe that was
the type he goes for at first.

556
00:27:35,353 --> 00:27:37,288
And that made me think,
"Maybe I'm not his type."

557
00:27:37,355 --> 00:27:39,557
But he also said he dated
someone shorter than him before.

558
00:27:39,624 --> 00:27:41,359
Yeah, he said that recently.

559
00:27:41,426 --> 00:27:43,428
I've dated people of different heights.

560
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:46,798
- I even dated someone who was 1 meter 62.
- Really?

561
00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:48,733
So you're not picky about height?

562
00:27:49,534 --> 00:27:52,704
I tend to prefer people
with defined features.

563
00:27:52,771 --> 00:27:53,772
Mmm.

564
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:55,340
Okay.

565
00:27:57,075 --> 00:27:58,476
In my heart…

566
00:27:58,543 --> 00:28:00,912
- No, I…
- So you thought you had a chance?

567
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:01,980
Well, yeah, I did.

568
00:28:02,047 --> 00:28:03,748
He likes people with defined features.

569
00:28:03,815 --> 00:28:05,450
- I definitely qualify.
- You qualify.

570
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:09,154
- I was like, "I fit his checklist."
- Yeah.

571
00:28:09,220 --> 00:28:12,524
Like you said earlier, my short-term goal
is to convey "I see you."

572
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:14,359
- You need an "I see you" time.
- Yeah.

573
00:28:14,993 --> 00:28:17,595
Yeah. Please, go next.

574
00:28:17,662 --> 00:28:20,565
I'm going to tell you everything,
no holding back. Okay?

575
00:28:20,632 --> 00:28:21,499
- Sure.
- Wait.

576
00:28:21,566 --> 00:28:23,468
- I'll be completely honest.
- Tell us.

577
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:27,672
I sensed that you two were talking
the day we went to Niseko.

578
00:28:27,739 --> 00:28:29,541
- At night.
- Yeah. Well, yeah.

579
00:28:29,607 --> 00:28:32,110
And, as you know,
I had feelings for Huwei too.

580
00:28:32,177 --> 00:28:33,878
- Mmm.
- I don't know.

581
00:28:33,945 --> 00:28:37,282
I mean, Hiroya, you're good-looking too.

582
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:39,417
You never know.
You never know in life.

583
00:28:39,484 --> 00:28:41,119
- Right?
- Did you hear that? "Too."

584
00:28:41,186 --> 00:28:43,822
- You're good-looking too.
- "I'm good-looking too."

585
00:28:44,489 --> 00:28:46,758
- Wait. I mean…
- "You're good-looking too."

586
00:28:46,825 --> 00:28:49,194
- You're good-looking too. You never know.
- You said "too."

587
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:50,395
- You never know.
- Yeah.

588
00:28:50,462 --> 00:28:52,197
- You never know how people feel.
- Sure.

589
00:28:52,263 --> 00:28:55,066
So, after that,
when we came back, I called Huwei.

590
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:56,801
- Oh, you did?
- And told him.

591
00:28:57,302 --> 00:28:59,704
But all he said was, "I'm happy."

592
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:01,072
Ah. Hmm.

593
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,441
Then you left, right?

594
00:29:03,508 --> 00:29:05,610
And after that, we went on a date.

595
00:29:05,677 --> 00:29:07,078
Mmm.

596
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:11,182
And now,
he told me that he might like me a little.

597
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:14,753
- Okay, I see. Okay, okay.
- He said he might like me a little.

598
00:29:15,386 --> 00:29:18,256
- Well, it's up to his feelings now.
- You're right.

599
00:29:18,323 --> 00:29:21,960
- Yeah, I'm ready whenever he is.
- Yeah, he's kind of hard to read.

600
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:24,696
<i>I know it's really crazy.</i>

601
00:29:25,997 --> 00:29:29,267
But you'll never guess
who showed up in my dream last night.

602
00:29:29,334 --> 00:29:30,368
Huwei.

603
00:29:31,102 --> 00:29:34,539
We were traveling somewhere,
and we were laughing together.

604
00:29:35,740 --> 00:29:38,443
Mmm. I was really happy.

605
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:41,012
Wow, he showed up in his dream!

606
00:29:43,014 --> 00:29:45,450
- It was cold today.
- Yeah, it really was.

607
00:29:46,484 --> 00:29:49,320
- This is nice.
- Oh, nice. It was a good idea, right?

608
00:29:49,387 --> 00:29:51,289
A great idea. It's like a good luck charm.

609
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:52,824
That's <i>what he wanted to do.</i>

610
00:29:52,891 --> 00:29:56,227
I'll keep this picture of you,
and you'll keep this one of me.

611
00:29:56,294 --> 00:29:57,862
It looks really great.

612
00:29:57,929 --> 00:29:59,564
<i>That is so sweet.</i>

613
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:03,268
I know we talked about it a little
during our overnight date,

614
00:30:03,334 --> 00:30:05,036
but what's your take on our future?

615
00:30:05,103 --> 00:30:08,540
Are you more anxious
or more excited about it?

616
00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:11,743
Excited, but it's like…

617
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:14,779
My parents…

618
00:30:16,347 --> 00:30:17,415
are strict.

619
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:21,152
I don't think that they imagined
that their son would

620
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,822
turn out to be like this.

621
00:30:26,057 --> 00:30:28,493
So, it won't be easy.

622
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:30,061
But…

623
00:30:30,929 --> 00:30:33,932
with you,
I think I might be able to overcome it.

624
00:30:33,998 --> 00:30:34,899
Mmm.

625
00:30:36,901 --> 00:30:39,737
I mean, you obviously won't be a woman…

626
00:30:40,538 --> 00:30:43,074
like my parents would have expected.

627
00:30:45,543 --> 00:30:49,981
Mmm. But I want them to know
that their son is happy

628
00:30:50,048 --> 00:30:53,484
and that they can rest easy
about his future.

629
00:30:54,619 --> 00:30:58,223
I also want to be able to tell
them how much I care about you.

630
00:30:58,990 --> 00:31:05,063
Yeah, I really want to tell them how
much I love you and put them at ease.

631
00:31:07,232 --> 00:31:09,901
- It might not be easy.
- You're right.

632
00:31:10,668 --> 00:31:12,070
But that's…

633
00:31:14,339 --> 00:31:15,340
okay.

634
00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:19,344
But even if it's not okay,

635
00:31:20,678 --> 00:31:22,347
I know I'm not alone,
and that's reassuring.

636
00:31:22,413 --> 00:31:23,348
Yeah.

637
00:31:23,848 --> 00:31:26,684
I know that I have someone by my side

638
00:31:27,819 --> 00:31:28,820
who supports me.

639
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:29,721
Mmm.

640
00:31:29,787 --> 00:31:31,189
If I'm thrown out, then…

641
00:31:32,624 --> 00:31:34,726
- You'll just have to keep trying, right?
- Yeah.

642
00:31:37,128 --> 00:31:38,596
We'll get through this.

643
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:40,798
I'm sure we can.

644
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:44,269
<i>I'd be so happy</i>
<i>if someone said that to me.</i>

645
00:31:44,335 --> 00:31:45,970
- <i>I know.</i>
- Thanks.

646
00:31:55,647 --> 00:31:57,248
It felt like a long time.

647
00:31:57,315 --> 00:31:59,250
It stirred up a lot of emotions.

648
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:03,688
I mean, this was
a whole new experience for me.

649
00:32:04,188 --> 00:32:07,759
Focusing on myself
and on the person I like,

650
00:32:07,825 --> 00:32:10,428
all day and every day going forward.

651
00:32:11,129 --> 00:32:15,833
So while it seems short-lived
when you measure it in time,

652
00:32:16,334 --> 00:32:18,469
each day was extremely packed.

653
00:32:19,637 --> 00:32:22,907
So it felt long, but in a good way. Mmm.

654
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,045
- Mmm.
- Very well said.

655
00:32:27,111 --> 00:32:29,647
I don't think you see many dating shows

656
00:32:29,714 --> 00:32:31,683
where people imagine their future

657
00:32:31,749 --> 00:32:33,985
after they get together
with the person they find.

658
00:32:34,052 --> 00:32:36,621
- Getting together is almost like the goal.
- Yeah.

659
00:32:36,688 --> 00:32:40,725
I'm very interested in how they'll
nurture their relationship afterwards.

660
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:42,727
Since he had been
with another guy before,

661
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:44,696
William had already been concerned

662
00:32:44,762 --> 00:32:47,498
about what his parents might think
of this situation.

663
00:32:47,565 --> 00:32:49,467
Well, this is a problem
that everyone faces.

664
00:32:49,534 --> 00:32:52,503
Despite the circumstances,
William and Izaya told each other,

665
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:55,039
"I believe I can overcome
this problem with you."

666
00:32:55,106 --> 00:32:58,309
- Being able to do that is truly wonderful.
- That's amazing.

667
00:32:58,376 --> 00:33:01,112
- That would make anyone happy.
- It would.

668
00:33:01,179 --> 00:33:05,183
Because of those worries, he probably
wanted to hear something reassuring.

669
00:33:05,249 --> 00:33:08,486
To feel a sense of certainty
and stability in his life.

670
00:33:08,553 --> 00:33:12,357
Meanwhile, Bomi, Jobu, and Hiroya
were catching up with each other,

671
00:33:12,423 --> 00:33:14,325
but I didn't know Taeheon
did such a thing.

672
00:33:14,392 --> 00:33:17,228
He's really messing with Jobu.
What's he trying to do?

673
00:33:17,295 --> 00:33:21,733
So, Jobu backed off once already, right?
He said he couldn't go for it anymore.

674
00:33:21,799 --> 00:33:23,468
Maybe that made Taeheon feel lonely.

675
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:27,839
Like, "He was approaching me,
but now he's not and it's a bit lonely. "

676
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:29,674
- Such a princess.
- "Don't give up."

677
00:33:29,741 --> 00:33:31,309
- A princess.
- A grand princess.

678
00:33:31,376 --> 00:33:32,877
That's a grand princess thing to do.

679
00:33:32,944 --> 00:33:36,014
But it made Jobu's heart flutter.
It made him go, "Huh?"

680
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:39,584
It made him want to invite Taeheon
to run the coffee truck with him again.

681
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:41,586
I hope that Taeheon

682
00:33:41,652 --> 00:33:45,189
will start to change his
romantic attitude little by little.

683
00:33:45,256 --> 00:33:47,325
- At least for Jobu's sake.
- Yeah.

684
00:33:47,392 --> 00:33:50,061
- Then there were Huwei's wonderful…
- Those two were awesome.

685
00:33:50,128 --> 00:33:53,264
- They were awesome. So funny.
- I really liked them. Even a brief scene.

686
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:57,301
They said, if he goes for the <i>o soto gari,</i>
he shouldn't hesitate at all.

687
00:33:57,368 --> 00:34:00,038
- His mentors were just awesome.
- That was such great advice.

688
00:34:00,104 --> 00:34:02,673
- Huwei was worried about that? Who knew?
- Yeah.

689
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:06,911
Because it's Bomi's first time, he didn't
know how things should move forward.

690
00:34:06,978 --> 00:34:10,581
We also got to learn something
deep about Huwei, thanks to them.

691
00:34:10,648 --> 00:34:12,650
You could tell that
he really trusts his friends.

692
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,986
- He's close to both his mentors.
- For sure.

693
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:18,723
Those two were great. I'd love
to go to a bar in Ebisu with them.

